1. *Kaput* je oštećen poput starog stola. (The cloth is damaged just like an old table.)

2. Njegovom *kaputu* treba popravka. (His coat needs repair.) 

3. Ona je bacila *kaput* u kantu za smeće. (She threw her coat in the trash can.)

4. *Kaputi* bili su suvišni na njenom slučaju. (The coats were unnecessary on her case.)

5. *Kaputom* se pokrivao da se zaštiti od kiše. (He covered himself with a coat to protect himself from the rain.)